    "value": "The **NVIDIA Nemotron-3-Super-120B-A12B** is a state-of-the-art open large language model (LLM) released in March 2026, designed for advanced agentic reasoning, coding, long-context tasks, and high-volume workflows (e.g., IT ticket automation, tool use, and retrieval-augmented generation). Here’s a detailed description of its features and architecture:\n\n---\n\n### Architecture\n- **Hybrid Model**: Combines Mamba-2 (for linear-time sequence processing), Mixture-of-Experts (MoE), and select Attention layers.\n- **LatentMoE**: Novel MoE variant that compresses each token's representation before expert routing; allows 512 experts with top-22 routing at the compute cost of a much smaller model.\n- **Multi-Token Prediction (MTP)**: Enables the model to generate several tokens per forward pass, improving speed and efficiency.\n- **Parameter Size**: 120B total parameters, with only 12B active per inference pass for improved compute efficiency.\n- **Context Length**: Natively supports up to 1 million tokens — among the longest context windows available, ensuring memory retention over very long tasks【3:6†source】【3:7†source】【3:8†source】.\n\n### Training and Data\n- **Pre-training Corpus**: Trained on 25 trillion tokens, including high-quality curated and synthetic text in 20+ natural languages and 43 programming languages.\n- **Data Freshness**: Pre-training cutoff is June 2025, and post-training data includes updates to February 2026【3:6†source】.\n- **Precision**: Trained in NVFP4 precision (native 4-bit floating point), enhancing efficiency.\n\n### Performance \u0026 Use Cases\n- **Throughput**: Achieves up to 2.2–7.5x higher throughput than comparable models; outputs up to 442 tokens/second depending on provider/hardware.\n- **Reasoning Mode**: Can be enabled/disabled or tuned for full, low-effort, or off, tailoring performance for complex or simple requests.\n- **Benchmarks**: Scores competitively with top models like Qwen3.5-122B and GPT-OSS-120B on agentic and general knowledge tasks【3:5†source】.\n- **Best For**: Agentic workflows, collaborative agents, software development, cybersecurity, long-form research, tool calling, long-context summarization, and IT automation【3:9†source】.\n\n### Supported Languages\n- English, French, German, Italian, Japanese, Spanish, Chinese\n- 43 programming languages\n\n### Deployment\n- **Hardware Requirements**: Minimum single NVIDIA B200 GPU (NVFP4), 2x H100 (FP8), or 4x A100 (BF16) for different variants.\n- **Licensing**: Open weights, datasets, and recipes under the NVIDIA Nemotron Open Model License permitting commercial use (compliance with safety guardrails required).\n\n### API \u0026 Pricing (as of 2026)\n- **Provider Inference Pricing**: Around $0.20–$0.75 per million tokens, depending on the platform.\n- **API Features**: Reasoning traces, tool calls, JSON output, streaming responses, and more.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:**  \nNemotron-3-Super-120B-A12B is a highly efficient, large-scale open-weight LLM purpose-built for agentic, reasoning-intensive workflows and massive context windows. It brings together innovative architecture (Mamba, MoE, MTP), high-quality multilingual/data training, and unmatched compute efficiency, setting a new standard for open-source LLMs in 2026【3:0†source】【3:3†source】【3:6†source】【3:7†source】【3:8†source】【3:9†source】.",
